>Then why is he the most played support in all of League, including international competitive scenes? You're implying that if he can't ever land his hook he can't do much. But it just takes 1 hook to secure a kill, and it happens a couple of times a game.

So many holes in this arguement

>But it just takes 1 hook to secure a kill, and it happens a couple of times a game.

But it takes just 1 stun to secure a kill {{champion:1}} 

But it takes just 1 hook to secure a kill {{champion:53}} 

But it takes just 1 Pole to secure a kill {{champion:48}} 

But it takes just 1 stun to secure a kill {{champion:89}} 

But it takes just 1 binding to secure a kill {{champion:25}} 

But it takes just 1 snare to secure a kill {{champion:99}} 

You're literally arguing that Thresh is overpowered because he has a form of cc.
